So, the rationale behind the game!

I wanted to make a game where it was hard to prove someone to be Evil because of power roles, but not impossible to use the information you did have to help inform voting. As always, I was hoping that hunting people through voting records and patterns might occur, but I should stop hoping at this point :P
This was the starting set up (except the Medium didn't get their rune until N2):

Djinn - Fjat rune  Furie Witch - Fjat rune Alchemist - Philosopher's stone - steel armour Harpy VD Medium - Fjat rune Cunning Ghoul - Steel Armour Cunning Ghoul VM - Fjat rune  Maple Wolf Maple Wolf Prot Witch Hunter - steel armour Stalker Stalker Stalker Militia Militia  Reviver - Restoration Pot Gravedigger Gravedigger Novice Tarot Reader Beholder Graverobber Graverobber Rune Smith Drunk - Fjat rune

I wanted the majority of the KP in the game to be from the village side, which would hopefully make people paranoid about village killing claims, and for most of the village roles to be things that Evil will claim when caught, and/or be Fam roles. I also thought multiple of each role would make the holders of those roles sus each other.
So, what didn't go according to my expectations?
Firstly, I allowed RNG to pick all the roles, because I would rather there was not meta expectations on people or myself.

That meant that Phy rolled VM and she wasn't really confident in her ability to shift people, so didn't want to collect Fams until the numbers were reduced a bit. I had counted on at least 1-2 villages being Fammed in the first 4-6 days in my set-up, so because that didn't happen, Village had more PRs than expected.

It also meant that people weren't really sus that there was a VM in the game, and so the Stalkers, Militias and GDs came under less suspicion than I expected them too. I probably should have put a Mortician in the set to ratchet up that paranoia
I also expected a LOT more deaths, so although there were 3 deaths on N2, there were less than I was expecting, as both Maples and the VM killed the Zombie, who was obviously already going to die.

I was hoping/expecting about 4-6 deaths on that day, and then probably 3-5 on N4 too. That would have been 7-11 deaths, and we had 6, one of which was the Zombie dying because the VD had been lynched, so wasn't a real death.
As mentioned above, Phy also killed the Zombie twice, two Evuls, and two village, and I anticipated more Village deaths from the Vampire than happened in the overall game.

None of the three neutrals that were in the game had any benefit either, which meant that I wasn't able to dynamically rebalance with the one Drunk, and also didn't have the game balance itself via the two GRs, which was unfortunate (albeit a GR did try to rob the VDs grave, but that bounced).

The way things turned out, it was a real challenge for Coven and Undead to win this game, and both teams mentioned that they felt underpowered, so my apologies to those who were Evil, because I think you were underpowered in the circumstances, and I had no way to correct for it. I do think that the majority of times this set was run, it would be relatively balanced in terms of outcome, although each individual game would likely be fairly swingy; this was just one of the ones that swung heavily to Good.

But thanks to you all for playing, I'd love to hear your thoughts on both the experience, and my expectations, and I hope that it was enjoyable for the majority of you. Also sorry/not sorry for the theme, because I really love the theme, but hadn't considered how infuriating it would be to try and find posts by hug, lug, rug, and bug. And apologies for Billbug being the only one capitalised, that was an error
